  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-AR-03 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. A binding requirement mandates experimental-validation as the required verification method for hemolysis output comparison; however, the supporting validation activity was conducted as a literature-review of published hemolysis datasets, and the validation result is traceable only to that activity. The narrative describes the literature survey as complementary evidence sufficient to satisfy the output-comparison requirement, but the structured activityType disagrees with the requiredVerificationMethod, breaking the inference link (W-AR-03).",
