    "name": "Output comparison must be supported by experimental validation",
    "description": "For Model Risk Level 5 Class III device assessments, the output-comparison credibility factor shall be substantiated by direct experimental-validation activities in which CFD-predicted hemolysis index values are compared against measured in-vitro or in-vivo data obtained under conditions representative of the COU. Literature surveys alone are not sufficient to satisfy this requirement.",
