      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Hemolysis output comparison via published literature survey",
      "description": "A comprehensive survey of 14 peer-reviewed publications reporting hemolysis index measurements for centrifugal blood pumps was conducted. CFD-predicted normalized index of hemolysis (nIH) values from the present model were compared against the range of nIH values reported in the surveyed literature. The survey found that model predictions fall within the interquartile range of published experimental results, supporting the conclusion that the model produces plausible hemolysis estimates. This evidence is considered complementary to the CFD analysis and sufficient to close the output-comparison credibility factor.",
